<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Booming South China Economy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, July 15 (Xinhua) -- Guangzhou, capital of south
China's Guangdong province, had a GDP of 73.7 billion yuan in the
first half of this year, 13 per cent more than that of the same
period last year.
</P>
<P>
The value of the city's exports was above 3.8 billion
U.S. dollars, 48.3 per cent more than the figure last year, and
1.4 billion U.S. dollars worth of overseas investment had been
used, 6.9 per cent increase.
</P>
<P>
The city's mayor Lin Shusen said today at a conference on local
economy that its economic structure has improved, with more
investment going to things like agriculture, high-tech industries
and infrastructure.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
