<HEADLINE> Xinhua International News Summary at 1600 GMT, July 15 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE -- Serbian President Slobodan Milosevic, whose mandate
expires soon, was elected today as president of the Federal
Republic of Yugoslavia by both chambers of the federal parliament.
</P>
<P>
Milosevic will serve as the top leader of Yugoslavia, which
comprises Serbia and Montenegro, for four years. He takes over
from the incumbent president Zoran Lilic. Milosevic will formally
take office at an extraordinary session of parliament on July 23.
</P>
<P>
BEIJING -- Premier Li Peng, meeting today with Do Muoi, general
secretary of the Vietnamese Communist Party (VCP) Central
Committee, said that the two countries' leaders have met several
times since Do Muoi visited China in November 1995 and these have
played an important role in the development of relations between
the two parties and the two countries.
</P>
<P>
He said that official talks between Jiang Zemin and Do Muoi on
Monday were "rich in content" and had "profound significance" for
the future development of relations and that promoting the
expansion of friendship and cooperation between the two countries
is not only in the basic interests of the two peoples, but also
benefits peace and stability in the region and the world as a
whole.
</P>
<P>
DHAKA -- The overall flood situation improved further today due
to stoppage of heavy downpour in most parts of Bangladesh and
resultant fall in the flow of most rivers in the Meghna and
southeastern hill basins.
</P>
<P>
According to the Flood Information Center, the overall flood
situation in southern Chittagong, Cox's Bazar, Bandarban and
Khagrachhari districts is expected to improve further today while
the flood situation in some northern districts will start
improving.
</P>
<P>
However, the center forecast that more areas of northwestern
Kurigram and Sirajganj districts may be inundated. 
</P>
</TEXT>
