<HEADLINE> Former Posts and Telecommunications Minister Passes Away </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 15 (Xinhua) -- Wen Minsheng, former minister of
Posts and Telecommunications, died of illness on June 24 at the
age of 82.
</P>
<P>
Wen's remains were cremated this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Wen was a member of the former Central Advisory Commission of
the Chinese Communist Party Central Committee.
</P>
<P>
President Jiang Zemin, Premier Li Peng and other Chinese
leaders including Qiao Shi, Li Ruihuan, Zhu Rongji, Liu Huaqing
and Hu Jintao expressed their condolences over Wen's death.
</P>
</TEXT>
