<BODY>
<HEADLINE> German Ullrich Wins 10th Stage </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 15 (Xinhua) -- Germany's Jan Ullrich of Germany won
the 10th stage of the Tour de France and took the leader's yellow
jersey as the competition went to Arcalis, Andorra, on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The German won the 252 kilometers stage, the longest mountain
stage of the Tour, clocking seven hour 46 minutes.
</P>
<P>
Marco Pantani of Italy and Richard Virenque of France were 67
seconds behind Ullrich.
</P>
<P>
Virenque moved to second overall, ahead of Denmark's Bjarne
Riis, who finished three minutes 22 seconds behind Ullrich to be
fifth in the stage.
</P>
<P>
The 23-year-old German unleashed a devastating attack 10
kilometers from the finish to break away from the others in the
leading pack.
</P>
<P>
Cedric Vasseur, who had worn the yellow jersey for five days,
made a series of attempts in vain to keep up with Ullrich.
</P>
<P>
Wednesday's 11th stage of 192 kilometers takes the Tour to
Perpignan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
