<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Fashion Designer Versace Shot Dead in Miami </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 15 (Xinhua) -- World-renowned fashion designer
Gianni Versace was shot to death today outside his mansion on
Miami Beach, Florida, said reports from Miami Beach.
</P>
<P>
Jackson Memorial Hospital said the Italian fashion designer,
50, was shot in the head at close range.
</P>
<P>
Police were seeking a white man aged about 25 who approached
Versace and shot him in the back of the head at the gates of the
mansion when Versace was returning to his home from a nearby
restaurant on the Ocean Drive strip.
</P>
<P>
Versace, who dressed some of the world's most beautiful women,
was not a permanent resident of Miami Beach but frequently stayed
at the white stone mansion, the most sumptuous private residence
in the area.
</P>
<P>
Along with Giorgio Armani, Versace was considered Italy's
leading ready-to-wear designer and a symbol of Italian fashion.
</P>
<P>
A native of Reggio Calabria in southern Italy, he began
designing ready-to-wear for other firms in 1972 in Milan. He
launched the Gianni Versace label with an autumn-winter collection
in 1978.
</P>
<P>
Besides women's and men's wear, his lines include children's
clothing, lingerie, beachwear, accessories and perfume. He also
designed fabrics, linens and chinaware. He gained fame in the
1980s. 
</P>
</TEXT>
