<DOCNO> XIE19970716.0013 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> UNICEF Puts Forth Suggestion for Curbing Child </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, July 15 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations Children
Fund (UNICEF), in a press release here today that 20-25 percent
of child deaths caused by malaria could be avoided if children
slept under bed-nets impregnated with insecticide.
</P>
<P>
The press release said that every year malaria causes the
deaths of one million children under five in Africa alone.
</P>
<P>
It said that dipping nets in the insecticide known as Pyrethroid
is more effective and practical than spraying the walls of the
home.
</P>
<P>
The UNICEF is launching a major renewed effort to prevent
malaria and provide care for its victims.
</P>
<P>
The UNICEF envisaged that every year the lives of 500,000
children in Africa will be saved by virtue of the new initiative
early in the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
The new initiative will support the global target of a 20
percent cut in malaria deaths by the year 2000 in at least 75
percent of affected countries, the release added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
