<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Arab Journalists Urge UN to Halt Israeli Aggression </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, July 15 (Xinhua) -- The Arab Journalists Union today
called on the United Nations and international human rights
organizations to force Israel to halt its "criminal aggression"
and "punitive measures" in Palestine.
</P>
<P>
The Egyptian MENA news agency reported today that in a
statement, the union said the Israeli "criminal campaign" against
unarmed Palestinians and Palestinian journalists in particular is
aimed to thwart the uprisings against Israel's intransigent
policies.
</P>
<P>
Five Palestinian journalists employed by foreign news media
were among 16 Arabs wounded by Israeli troops in clashes in the
divided West Bank city of Hebron on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The Palestinians accused the Israeli army of deliberately
shooting the journalists on duty, but the Israeli side denied the
charges.
</P>
<P>
The union called upon the International Journalists Union to
support it in its campaign for defending the freedom of speech.
</P>
<P>
Violence and demonstrations have become a daily scene in the
occupied Palestinian territories since Israeli-Palestinian peace
talks collapsed after Israel broke ground on a Jewish settlement
in East Jerusalem four months ago. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
