<DOCNO> XIE19970716.0016 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Museveni Launches Development Blueprint for </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, July 15 (Xinhua) -- Ugandan President Yoweri Museveni
today launched a 1.5 million U.S. Dollars project to establish
a development strategy for the next 25 years code-named
"Uganda Vision 2025".
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the launching ceremony, Museveni said that
launching the vision 2025 provides an opportunity for all
Ugandans to participate in the planning of the development of the
country.
</P>
<P>
He said all of the Ugandans is being asked to participate in the
determination of the direction that the country should follow in
its development.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, he said, "this will form a framework within which
our progress as a nation can be accessed."
</P>
<P>
He called upon all Ugandans to contribute towards this
endeavor with total commitment.
</P>
<P>
With the launching of the vision, Uganda became the 16th
African country to embark on such a venture. It is the first ever
national long-term perspective studies (NLTPS) which is funded by
the United Nations Development Program.
</P>
<P>
A Uganda 2025 national core team will be charged with the
responsibility of consulting widely among Ugandans on the
18-month NLTPS project.
</P>
<P>
On the same occasion, Museveni also launched the 1997 Ugandan
human development report aiming at improving Ugandan quality of
living. 
</P>
</TEXT>
