<HEADLINE> Timber Industry's Turnover Increases in Zimbabwe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, July 15 (Xinhua) -- Zimbabwe's timber industry
registered an increase in turnover of 37.7 percent to 90 million
U.S. Dollars in the financial year ended in June.
</P>
<P>
Timber Producers Federation Chairman Bursary Mamvoto today
said the industry was undergoing further expansion involving huge
capital outlays.
</P>
<P>
This, he said, would result in a significant increase in the
production of sawn timber and in the demand for skilled
labor-force.
</P>
<P>
He said the drive for exports remained a strategic goal for
the industry which registered a 10 increase in exports this year.
</P>
<P>
Mamvoto said the area under commercial plantation in Zimbabwe
increased to 112,000 hectares this year after realizing a one
percent marginal increase.
</P>
<P>
He commended the government for giving the industry an
assurance that it would facilitate the expansion of its forestry
base.
</P>
<P>
Over the past year, the volume of timber log harvesting
increased by 6.3 percent to 1.32 million cubic meters, of which
three percent was exported as pulpwood. At the same time, sawn
timber production went up by 6.7 percent to 396,000 cubic meters.
</P>
</TEXT>
