<HEADLINE> Arafat Urges Europe to Play Bigger Role in Middle East </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, July 15 (Xinhua) -- Palestinian President Yasser Arafat
said here today that European countries should use the powerful
economic card in urging Israel to stop building new settlements in
occupied territories.
</P>
<P>
Addressing a London conference on Middle East, Arafat, who is
on a two-day visit to Britain, said, "Seventy percent of the
economy of Israel is with European countries and this card has not
been used until now."
</P>
