<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe Embarks on Five-year Housing Plan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, July 15 (Xinhua) -- The National Housing Construction
Trust, an affiliate of the Zimbabwe Government Employees Union
(ZIGEU), has embarked on a 336 million Zimbabwe Dollars (30.5
million U.S. Dollars) five-year plan to build 1,200 houses a
year.
</P>
<P>
ZIGEU Executive Director Witness Socks today said the trust
had targeted production of 100 houses a month countrywide to meet
demand for affordable accommodation by its 30,000 members.
</P>
<P>
