administrative framework to ensure a free and fair General
Election while religious leaders would make proposals for
consideration by the government.
</P>
<P>
President Moi agreed to meet religious leaders frequently
before the coming General Election to be held later this year to
continue the consultations.
</P>
<P>
During the past month, violence has been escalating as
opposition parties have repeatedly organized mass rallies in the
country to press for minimum constitutional reforms before the
General Election.
</P>
<P>
Today's meeting held at the Nairobi State House was the first
which President Moi had with religious leaders on reforms since
the start of an Opposition-backed campaign pressing for change.
