<HEADLINE> Forum Discussing Chinese President's Important Speech </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 16 (Xinhua) -- A forum was held in Beijing today
by "People's Daily" and "Seeking Truth" magazine, mouthpieces of
the Chinese Communist Party (CPC) Central Committee, on President
Jiang Zemin's recent speech urging the Chinese people to hold high
the banner of Deng Xiaoping.
</P>
<P>
Jiang spoke on May 29 to senior provincial and
ministerial-level officials who were attending the Party School of
the CPC Central Committee.
</P>
<P>
Theorists and ministerial-level officials at today's forum said
they agree that Jiang's speech came at an important moment in
Chinese history and offers guidelines for the 21st century.
Jiang's remark about holding high the banner of Deng Xiaoping's theory
of building socialism with Chinese Characteristics points to
the direction the Party should follow, they said.
</P>
<P>
The speech prepares the theoretical and ideological groundwork
for the Party's 15th national congress, and has great practical
and historical significance for uniting the Party and the people
nationwide.
</P>
<P>
They said that the matter of the banner is extremely important,
because it relates to the Party's and the nation's destiny, and
that Jiang has adhered to Deng's thought of seeking truth from
facts, which is helpful for the Party in solving problems, and in
providing a basis for drawing up Party's policies and decrees.
</P>
<P>
To make headway in economic system reforms, the banner must be
held high, they noted, and state-owned enterprise reforms will no
doubt make headway if we move forward boldly and practice
bravely in accordance with Deng's theory and Jiang's speech.
</P>
<P>
They also noted that improving the Party leadership, which was
something Jiang called for, is the fundamental guarantee in
pushing socialism into the next century. 
</P>
</TEXT>
