<HEADLINE> French Bank to Expand Business in Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 16 (Xinhua) -- Credit Agricole Indosuez, a
leading French merchant bank, has defined the Hong Kong market as
a priority in its global business expansion.
</P>
<P>
Jean-Claude Gruffat, chairman Asia-Pacific of Credit Agricole
Indosuez, said today, "Our bank seeks growth. Asia is the world's
fastest growing area, and that's why we bump into this area."
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong is the business front in Asia under the bank's new
strategy implemented since the first half of 1996. A level playing
field, least regulated economy, and a free and open financial
environment make Hong Kong the ideal choice, according to Gruffat.
</P>
<P>
Credit Agricole Indosuez came into being after Caisse Nationale
de Credit Agricole and Banque Indosuez integrated in June this
year. As the largest and most profitable branch of the newly
merged bank, the Hong Kong branch is active in all business lines
ranging from corporate financing to debt market, asset management,
equity business and private banking.  
</P>
