<HEADLINE> Top Seed Muster Upset at Mercedes Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, July 16 (Xinhua) -- Top seed Thomas Muster was upset in
his first match at the 1.04-million U.S. dollar Mercedes Cup in
Stuttgart on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Spaniard Alberto Portas downed the Austrian laycourt aura 6-4,
7-5 to move into the the third round.
</P>
<P>
Muster saved two match points in the 10th game of the second
set, but couldn't hold onto his momentum after levelling at 5-5.
</P>
<P>
World No. 52 Portas, who lost the Barcelona final in April to
fellow Spaniard Albert Costa, broke back for 6-5, then finished
the second-round upset in the next game when Muster sent a return
long.
</P>
<P>
Yevgeny Kafelnikov of Russia, beaten finalist here last year,
needed three sets to finally stop Frenchman Fabrice Santoro 2-6,
6-3, 6-4 in just under two hours. He next faces Saniard Francisco
Clavet, who beat 16th-seed Marc Rosset of Switzerland 7-5, 6-1.
</P>
<P>
Local favorite Boris Becker, the seventh seed playing here for
only the second time in his career, was aiming for the third
round, but had to get by difficult Moroccan Karim Alami in their
Centre Court showdown later on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Ninth-seed Albert Costa outlasted Slava Dosedel of the Czech
Republic 6-3, 7-5, while his 10th-seeded compatriot Felix Mantilla
ousted Fernando Melegeni of Brazil 6-4, 6-4.
</P>
<P>
Swede Magnus Larsson dismissed 13th-seeded Greg Rusedski 7-6
(7/4), 6-7 (2/7), 6-4. 
