<HEADLINE> Cambodia's FM Says He Will Replace Ranariddh as First PM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH, July 16 (Xinhua) -- Cambodia's Foreign Minister Ung
Hout said today that he was willing to accept the job of first
prime minister, replacing Prince Norodum Ranariddh who was ousted
by his rival, Second Prime Minister Hun Sen last week.
</P>
<P>
Ung Hout, a senior member of First Prime Minister Ranariddh's
FUNCINPEC party, said he still respected Ranariddh, but put the
interests of the people and the country first.
</P>
<P>
"I accept to be first prime minister because I put the
interests of my people and my country first," he told reporters.
</P>
<P>
He added that 10 million Cambodian people didn't want the
current turbulent situation to continue.
</P>
<P>
The foreign minister said he would actively cooperate with Hun
Sen to tackle the problems facing Cambodia as soon as his
appointment was ratified by the National Assembly.
</P>
<P>
He said as long as everything was done in accordance with the
Constitution and laws, the international community would respond
and the situation in Cambodia would take a turn for the better.
</P>
<P>
Ranariddh was ousted on Sunday July 6 while he was in Paris
after a weekend of fighting in the Cambodian capital between
troops loyal to him, and forces loyal to Second Prime Minister Hun
Sen.
</P>
<P>
But Hun Sen said he wanted the coalition government between his
Cambodian People's Party (CPP) and the FUNCINPEC to remain in
place and for FUNCINPEC to choose a new first prime minister to
replace Ranariddh.
</P>
<P>
The CPP would support Ung Hout's nomination in the National
Assembly, an adviser to Hun Sen said.
</P>
<P>
"We feel that he is acceptable," Hun Sen's adviser Om Yentieng
told reporters.
</P>
<P>
Earlier today, FUNCINPEC officials said they agreed on Ung
Hout's nomination for the post of first prime minister.
</P>
<P>
Ung Hout's nomination will be submitted to the National
Assembly for approval when it reconvenes on July 28. 
</P>
</TEXT>
