<DOCNO> XIE19970716.0064 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-16 15:32 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Iraq Cleared of Implication in Death of Kuwaiti Boy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, July 16 (Xinhua) -- Investigations have cleared Iraqis
of implication in the death of a Kuwaiti boy in a plush Cairo
hotel Tuesday, the Egyptian MENA news agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
Major General Ahmad Hammam Ateya, security chief of Giza, where
the hotel is located, told a press conference that the death of
the Kuwaiti child was caused by asphyxiation and not by alleged
play of Iraqi agents.
</P>
<P>
The four-year-old child drowned Tuesday in the room's bathtub
of Pyramisa Hotel where his family was staying. His mother had
alleged that she woke up to find her boy dead in the room with a
note scrawled on the wall.
</P>
<P>
The message, addressed to the Kuwaiti Emir, suggests the
implication of Iraqi agents in the death.
</P>
<P>
At the press conference, Ateya refuted reports by foreign news
media that the boy was deliberately killed in the hotel's swimming
pool and then taken to the room he shared with his family.
</P>
<P>
He said that the police found in the room two pens that were
used to write the message, and the mother later recanted her
statement and confessed she had lied for fear of being charged
with negligence and of retaliation from the boy's father, he
added.
</P>
<P>
Iraq and Kuwait have been at odds since Iraq invaded this Gulf
neighbor in 1990. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
