<HEADLINE> Vietnamese Leader Visits Southwestern Chinese Border Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, July 16 (Xinhua) -- Vietnamese Communist Party (VCP)
General Secretary Do Muoi arrived in the capital of China's Yunnan
province, which borders Vietnam, today, and met with the Secretary
of the Provincial Communist Party Committee Gao Yan and Governor
He Zhiqiang this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Gao said that the friendship between Yunnan's people and the
Vietnamese people has a long history, and that trade and economic
co-operation between the two sides have grown rapidly in recent
years.
</P>
<P>
He said that Do Muoi's visit will promote co-operation and
exchanges between the two sides, and he invited the Vietnamese to
attend a world gardening fair to be held in Kunming in 1999.
</P>
<P>
Do Muoi said that the major goal of his visit is to expand
co-operation between the two sides.
</P>
<P>
Also present at the meeting were Li Shuzheng, head of the
International Department of the CPC Central Committee, He
Zhiqiang, deputy-secretary of the Provincial CPC Committee, and
Phan Van Khai, a member of the Political Bureau of the VCP Central
Committee and deputy premier.
</P>
<P>
The governor held a separate meeting with Phan Van Khai this
afternoon. The two sides expressed confidence in the future of
economic co-operation and social contacts between Yunnan and
Vietnam.
</P>
<P>
Phan said that Do Muoi's visit to Yunnan, the second leg of his
China trip, shows his interest in promoting trade and economic
co-operation. He said that Vietnamese entrepreneurs accompanying
Do Muoi will hold discussions and sign agreements and contracts
with business people in Yunnan. Both sides will create conditions
to support their co-operation.  
</P>
</TEXT>
