<HEADLINE> HK Students Set Off for Training in Inland Area </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 16 (Xinhua) -- A total of 175 students of the
Chinese University of Hong Kong departed today for study and
training programs in Beijing, Guangzhou, Huizhou, Shenzhen and
Dongguan.
</P>
<P>
These students are participants of the University's China
Career Development Award Program, which is the most organized
program aiming at equipping students with knowledge of and working
experience in contemporary China among local tertiary
institutions, a release from the University said today.
</P>
<P>
A four-week training course on contemporary China organized
with the assistance of Beijing University, Qinghua University and
Beijing Administrative College in Beijing will accept 100 of
these students, while six-week internships at various commercial
and cultural organizations in Beijing are arranged for another 40
students.
</P>
<P>
The other students will work in Shenzhen, Guangzhou and Huizhou
as interns in a variety of positions in banking, accountancy,
manufacturing, trading, shipping, property management and software
development.
</P>
<P>
Sponsors of internships include leading Hong Kong companies
with operations in inland areas as well as companies in other
parts of China.  
</P>
</TEXT>
