<HEADLINE> WHO Regional Office to Run Workshop in Zimbabwe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, July 16 (Xinhua) -- The World Health Organization
(WHO) regional office for Africa will hold a five-day workshop in
Harare from next Monday to develop guidelines for health
information, dissemination and promotion.
</P>
<P>
According to a WHO statement today, the workshop, to be
attended by delegates from 21 English-speaking countries, will
coincide with the launching of the regional office's newly
published "Health Information Package", a document dealing with
the prevention of 11 diseases prevalent in Africa.
</P>
<P>
"The deteriorating health situation in the African region has
sharply increased public need and demand for information on
health matters," the statement said, adding this has also
heightened the importance of the role of WHO as a major provider
of information. 
</P>
