<HEADLINE> Pakistan to Hold Population Census in October </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, July 16 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan has decided to hold
population census from October 18 to 31 this year.
</P>
<P>
The decision was made at a meeting of the federal cabinet held
here today and chaired by Prime Minister Nawaz Sharif, official
sources said.
</P>
<P>
The census will be conducted by officials of the provincial
governments and monitored by personnel of the armed and civil
armed forces.
</P>
<P>
The entire exercise is estimated to cost 841 million rupees (21
million U.S. dollars), according to the sources.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the meeting which was also attended by the
provincial chief ministers, Sharif expressed satisfaction over the
fact that the census will be conducted by his government with full
cooperation of the provincial governments.
</P>
<P>
He assured the provincial chief ministers that the federal
government will provide every possible help and assistance to the
provincial governments in the exercise, said the sources.
</P>
</TEXT>
