<HEADLINE> Beijing to Support Private Technology Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 16 (Xinhua) -- Beijing, China's captial city,
vows to provide support for the private technology industry as
indicated by a call by Jia Qinglin, mayor of Beijing, today in a
municipal seminar on science and technology, the 14th to be held.
</P>
<P>
At today's meeting, which is intended as a means for experts to
offer advice to municipal officials, the experts discussed the
problems that local private technology companies face and on how
to make better use of the firms.
</P>
<P>
Since China's first private technology business was established
in Beijing in October 1980, 11,847 such businesses have been set
up in the city, with more than 200,000 employees.
</P>
<P>
In 1996, these companies had an overall income of 32 billion
yuan and paid some 1.2 billion yuan in taxes.  
</P>
