<HEADLINE> China Cracks Down On Fake Goods </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 16 (Xinhua) -- Nine people involved in producing
and selling fake products have been sentenced to death in China
since the fall of 1995, when the country held its first national
conference on dealing with the problem of fake goods.
</P>
<P>
The third such conference was held via telephone today. It
revealed that the country has uncovered fake goods worth 5.8
billion yuan on the market and has sent some 400 people guilty of
making or selling bogus goods to prison in the past two
years. These goods include medicines, farm-use materials, cotton,
alcohols, cigarettes, and machinery.
</P>
<P>
Vice-premier Wu Bangguo sent a letter to the conference,
calling for further work in this area. 
</P>
