<HEADLINE> Injuried Kenya's Aguta Still Unconscious </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, July 16 (Xinhua) -- Kenya's marathon star Lameck Aguta
has been unconscious for four days by Wednesday after he was
admitted to hospital following a car accident last Sunday,
according to his twin brother Zachary Nyambaso.
</P>
<P>
Doctors said his condition was still stable and they would
issue a bulletin if there were any changes.
</P>
<P>
Kenyan Aguta, the Boston Marathon and also the Commonwealth
10,000 meters champion, sustained head injuries in the crash but a
brain scan showed no serious damage.
</P>
<P>
Doctors, who had said on Monday they were encouraged by his
condition, were concerned on Wednesday that the athlete was still
unconscious and that his condition remained largely unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Police said Aguta was injured when his car went out of control
and landed in a ditch in his native Rift Valley province. The
driver of the car and another man were slightly injured. 
</P>
