<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970716.0084 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 22 Students Missing in Northern Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, July 16 (Xinhua) -- Rescuers are trekking the 1,253
meter Mountain Natib, in the northern Philippines, to look for 22
university students who were missing after they went up the
mountain over the weekend, police sources said here today.
</P>
<P>
The sources said that the students, all club mountaineers of
the University of the Philippines, were reportedly trapped by a
landslide last Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The students made their last radio contact Monday when a Manila
amateur radio enthusiast received their signal for rescue, the
sources said.
</P>
<P>
They said that the amateur radio enthusiast informed the police
of the students' plight in Mountain Natib, Bataan province.
</P>
<P>
The rescuers, backed by helicopters, are scouring the mountain
on the island of Luzon for the missing students, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
