<DOCNO> XIE19970716.0085 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> S.Africa's Vodacom to Be Botswana Cellular phone </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, July 16 (Xinhua) -- Botswana Telecommunications
Corporation (BTC) has selected South Africa's largest cellular network
operator Vodacom as its joint venture partner in a bid for a license
to operate a cellular network in Botswana.
</P>
<P>
BTC Chief Executive Olebile Gaborone announced today in Gaborone,
capital of Botswana, that Vodacom had been selected because of its
experience in southern Africa, which could enable a cellular network
to be set up in Botswana relatively quickly.
</P>
<P>
The Botswana Telecommunications Authority (BTA) is expected to
make a decision on awarding the license in September this year.
</P>
<P>
Two licenses would be awarded and each successful tenderer will
have to pay one million Pula (about 280,000 US Dollar) for a 15 year
licence, said the BTA spokesman.
</P>
<P>
The BTA said it had tried to ensure that the network would cover a large
part of this vast, mostly desert country with a population of only 1.5
million people.
</P>
<P>
"The minimum requirements are that both operators will have to
establish a network that covers a mandatory section along the line of
rail and main road from Lobatse in the south to Francistown in the
north," the BTC spokesman added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
