<HEADLINE> Garment Factory Fire Kills 9 in Bangladesh </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, July 16 (Xinhua) -- At least nine persons were burnt to
death and five others injured when a devastating fire gutted a
garment factory Tuesday evening at Mirpur area in the capital city
of Dhaka, police sources said today.
</P>
<P>
Mirpur police said nine bodies were recovered today from inside
the garment factory while more bodies may remain under the debris.
</P>
<P>
The Rahman Garment is located at the fourth and fifth floors of
a six-storied building which caught fire at around 9 p.m. (local
time) Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Fire service vehicles rushed to the spot and extinguished the
fire at midnight.
</P>
<P>
The cause of the fire could not be confirmed yet, police added.
</P>
</TEXT>
