<HEADLINE> Japan Offers Kenya Grant for Food Production </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, July 16 (Xinhua) -- Japan will give Kenya a grant
worth 442 million Kenyan Shillings (7.65 million U.S. Dollars)
to boost Kenya's food production in accordance with an agreement
signed here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement signed between the two countries,the grant
will be used by Kenyan farmers to procure fertilizers,
agricultural chemicals and agricultural machinery.
</P>
<P>
Also on Tuesday, the Kenya Power Company signed an engineering
consultancy services contract with Nippon Koei Company of Japan
for the implementation of the 60-megawatt Sondu-Miriu hydro power
project.
</P>
<P>
The project, to be completed in 2002, will cost nine billion
Shillings (161.1 million U.S.Dollars) and is expected to ease
pressure on the current generating capacity in the country.
</P>
<P>
The Japanese government had extended to Kenya a loan of 3.6
billion Shillings (66.7 million Dollars) to fund the first phase
of the project earlier this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
