<HEADLINE> Deng Xiaoping's Hometown Remembers Him With Exhibition </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, July 16 (Xinhua) -- An exhibition on Deng
Xiaoping's achievements opened today in Guangan County, his
hometown in Sichuan Province in southwest China.
</P>
<P>
More than 500 government officials and public figures attended
today's opening ceremony.
</P>
<P>
It has a display of over 500 photos and 50 historical items of
the late Chinese leader, including manuscripts, everyday items,
and tools he used in east China's Jiangxi Province. The exhibition
has five sections that tells people more about the important
periods of Deng's life.
</P>
<P>
The three-day event is the country's largest exhibition on Deng
Xiaoping.  
</P>
</TEXT>
