<DOCNO> XIE19970716.0093 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-16 12:58 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Middle East Business Briefs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, July 16 (Xinhua) -- The following are business briefs
from Middle East countries.
</P>
<P>
NICOSIA -- The first half of this year saw a spectacular 27.8
percent increase in credit card spending in Cyprus, compared with
that of last year, and it reached 80.6 million Cyprus pounds
(about 161.2 million U.S. dollars), Cyprus Financial Mirror
reported today.
</P>
<P>
Spending with locally-issued cards in the first half of 1997
rose by 49 percent over the same period in 1996, standing at
47.7 million pounds (about 95.4 million dollars).
</P>
<P>
The sharp increase is attributed to the better awareness of
the Cypriot cardholders about the cards and the fact that credit
cards are now widely accepted at most retail outlets.
</P>
<P>
In addition, card-issuing banks have widened the choice of
cards offered to their customers, which in turn has enticed more
customers to resort to the use of plastic money, instead of the
traditional cash.
</P>
<P>
NICOSIA -- Trade between Greece and Cyprus has marked a rising
trend in recent years, totaling 171.6 million Cyprus pounds
(about 343.2 million U.S. dollars) in 1996 from 153.4 million
pounds (about 306.8 million dollars) in 1995, and 136.9 million
pounds (about 273.8 million dollars) in 1994, a Greek diplomat in
Cyprus said today.
</P>
<P>
Chrysanthi Passadi, economic and commercial attache of the
Greek Embassy in Nicosia told the press that exports of Greece,
which ranks the fourth among countries exporting to Cyprus,
account for 7.21 percent of the volume of the island's imports in
1996 against 7.18 percent in 1995 and 6.81 percent in 1994.
</P>
<P>
Cypriot exports to Greece, the island's fourth largest
foreign market, were 37.6 million Cyprus pounds (about 75.2
million U.S. dollars) in 1996 from 33.4 million pounds (about
66.8 million dollars) a year earlier.
</P>
<P>
AMMAN -- Former Jordanian prime minister Abdul Karim Kabariti
has been elected board chairman of the Jordan-Kuwait Bank here
at the bank's meeting, according to Jordan's news agency Petra.
</P>
<P>
The seven-member bank board also consists of three Kuwaitis
and three other Jordanians.
</P>
<P>
Kabariti has recently made important contributions in
attracting investors from Kuwait and other Arab countries to
raise the bank`s capital from 10 million Jordanian dinars (about
14 million U.S. dollars) to 20 million dinars (about 28 million
dollars).
</P>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY -- Kuwait's state reserves has registered an
increase of 21 percent during the past four years to reach 17
billion dinars (56.1 billion U.S. dollars) at the end of last May.
</P>
<P>
Kuwaiti Finance Minister Nasser Al-Roudhan attributed, at a
National Assembly session late last night, the increase to the
improved gain of returns for the Kuwaiti Reserve Fund for Future
Generations and the State Public Reserve which recorded 11.7
billion U.S. dollars during the period.
</P>
<P>
The minister said growth rate of the returns on the two
reserves were around 15 percent on average during these years.
</P>
<P>
He also declared that returns on the state investments in the
1996/97 fiscal year ending on June 30 even surpassed oil revenues
realized during 1995/96 fiscal year.
</P>
<P>
Oil revenues in 1995/96 in the oil-rich Gulf state were over 3
billion Kuwait dinars or about 10 billion U.S. dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970716.0094 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Official Calls Flood and Drought Precautions </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 16 (Xinhua) -- Vice-premier Jiang Chunyun told a
meeting here today that arrangement for possible big floods and
droughts in the near future must be made.
</P>
<P>
The current situation is already serious and officials must try
to guess the consequences, and should "mobilize people to join in
the work," he said.
</P>
<P>
China has been suffering badly from droughts in northern areas
and floods in the south this summer. Some 4.2 million hectares of
farmland have been affected by flood waters and heavy rains, and 38
million people have been mobilized daily to fight the drought.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that because of the El Nino influence from the
Pacific Ocean, various disasters may occur in China this year at
the same time, so the nation must be fully prepared.
</P>
<P>
Officials should be especially clear headed, he said, and the
nation must work hard for a good harvest by dealing with the
natural disasters.
</P>
<P>
He gave specific instructions for reservoir and flood
prevention projects, and ordered electric power, agriculture,
transportation, and civil affairs departments to provide aid.
</P>
<P>
"We must get good results in the work to greet the opening of
the Chinese Communist Party's 15th national congress," he
concluded.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
