<HEADLINE> Central Delegation to Mark Inner Mongolia's Anniversary </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 16 (Xinhua) -- A central delegation led by
Vice-premier Zou Jiahua will leave Beijing for Hohhot, the capital
of Inner Mongolia, tomorrow to attend the 50th anniversary
celebrations of the establishment of Inner Mongolia Autonomous
Region.
</P>
<P>
The members of the 80-member delegation are from the Central
Committee of the Chinese Communist Party, the Standing Committee
of the National People's Congress, the State Council, the National
Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative
Conference, the People's Liberation Army, All-China Federation of
Trade Unions, All-China Women's Federation, the Central Committee
of the Chinese Communist Youth League. and from provinces that
have close economic ties with Inner Mongolia.
</P>
<P>
Elsie Leong Oi-Sie, Secretary of Justice of the First
Government of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region, will
join the delegates.
</P>
<P>
Inner Mongolia became China's first autonomous region of
national minorities on May 1, 1947. 
</P>
