<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Becomes Vice-Chairman Of World Copyright Committee </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 16 (Xinhua) -- China was recently chosen as a
vice-chairman of UNESCO's 12th Meeting of the Governmental
Committee of the World Copyright Convention, the State Copyright
Administration revealed today.
</P>
<P>
This is the first time for China to hold the position, and its
highest so far in the World Copyright Convention, which it joined
in 1992. China became a member of the Governmental Committee of
the convention in 1995.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman for the SCA said that over the past five years
China has made considerable progress in fighting copyright piracy,
safeguarding the rights of copyright holders both inside and
outside China, and in increasing copyright controls.
</P>
<P>
He said that this achievement has been pointed to by many
countries and international organizations. The World Copyright
Convention has 97 members.  
</P>
</TEXT>
