<HEADLINE> Sri Lankan Ruling Party MPs Endorse Draft Constitution </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, July 16 (Xinhua) -- People's Alliance (PA)
parliamentarians and organizers unanimously endorsed the draft
constitution for Sri Lanka which seeks to devolve part of the
authority of the central government with a view to solving the
complex ethnic problem, according to a news release from the
Presidential Secretariat this evening.
</P>
<P>
The release said a resolution was adopted at a two-day workshop
held on Monday and Tuesday at Kalutara, over 20 kilometers from
Colombo.
</P>
<P>
The resolution said since the present Constitution of Sri Lanka
is wholly inadequate to promote a solution to the ethnic problem
which has emerged as the principal impediment to the progress of
the country and its people, and the achievement of justice, fair
play and democracy.
</P>
<P>
All PA MPs expressed their unanimous endorsement of the new
draft constitution which seeks to devolve part of the authority of
the central government as the basis of a solution to the complex
ethnic problem, while the war against the Tamil rebels is
vigorously prosecuted, the release noted.
</P>
<P>
This meeting offered its assistance and support for all
measures taken by the government to accomplish this objective, the
release added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
