<HEADLINE> Suspect in Slaying of Fashion Designer Identified </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 16 (Xinhua) -- More than 12 hours after
Italian fashion designer Gianni Versace was shot and killed at
Miami Beach in southern United States, Miami Beach police named
one of the Federal Bureau of Investigations' most wanted fugitives
as their leading suspect.
</P>
<P>
Beach police chief Richard Barreto identified the suspect as
Andrew Phillip Cunanan, 27, who was already being sought in the
slaying of four men from Minneapolis to New Jersey and was known
to move in gay circles.
</P>
<P>
Investigators said they didn't know of any previous link
between Cunanan and the designer who was gay.
</P>
<P>
Versace, 50, was returning home from the News Cafe on South
Beach's Ocean Drive after buying an Italian newspaper when he was
slain outside the gates of his Mediterranean-style mansion Tuesday
morning.
</P>
<P>
Authorities contacted gay and lesbian organizations in South
Florida to see if anyone recognized Cunanan. Police said he was a
male prostitute who frequented gay bars, and the FBI distributed
2,000 fliers with the suspect's picture and information about the
previous killings. 
</P>
</TEXT>
