<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Senior Party Official Meets With Japanese LDP Delegation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 16 (Xinhua) -- Hu Jintao, a senior official of
the Communist Party of China (CPC), meeting this afternoon with a
delegation from Japan's Liberal Democratic Party (LDP), headed by
its secretary-general Kato Koichi, said that the CPC is willing to
develop exchanges and cooperation with the LDP on the basis of the
four principles guiding party-to-party relations.
</P>
<P>
Hu is a member of the Standing Committee of the Political
Bureau and a member of the Secretariat, of the CPC Central
Committee.
</P>
<P>
In welcoming the delegation, he said that this year is the
25th anniversary of the normalization of Sino-Japanese diplomatic
relations. For the past 25 years, Sino-Japanese relations have
developed well and accomplished things that were not easily come
by.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that it is the historical responsibility of the
two countries' statesmen to remember both the positive and
negative historical experience and to review the past and looking
forward to the future, understand the general trends for the
development of bilateral relations on the basis of the principles
set forth in the Sino-Japanese Joint Statement and the Treaty of
Peace and Friendship to bring a long-term, sound and stable
Sino-Japanese good-neighborly friendship to the next century.
</P>
<P>
This is in the fundamental interests of the two peoples and
also conducive to peace, stability, and development in Asia and in
the world as a whole, he said.
</P>
<P>
Expressing his appreciation for Kato's contributions to
bilateral friendship, Hu said he hopes that both sides can make a
joint effort to increase mutual understanding and trust, and
remove interference, to push the development of Sino-Japanese
good-neighborly friendship farther forward.
</P>
<P>
Kato said that bilateral relations have developed smoothly in
general for the past 25 years, especially bilateral economic and
trade relations, which have had extensive development.
</P>
<P>
He said he hopes to further bilateral exchanges and
co-operation in various aspects like politics, to increase
exchanges between the two ruling parties, especially visits by
young statesmen, and to promote the establishment of a firm
bilateral friendship to make it conducive to the two countries,
and to peace and stability in Asia and the world.
</P>
<P>
He said that the older generation of statesmen of the two
countries have made a great effort in bilateral friendship, and
that his generation should make an effort to continue Japan-China
friendship from generation to generation as the earlier generation
did.
</P>
<P>
Kato and his party arrived here yesterday as guests of the CPC.
</P>
<P>
The head of the International Department of the CPC Central
Committee, Li Shuzheng, held discussions with the delegation
yesterday afternoon.  
</P>
</TEXT>
