<HEADLINE> Renminbi Deposits at China's Largest Bank Top Two Trillion </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 16 (Xinhua) -- The Industrial and Commercial Bank
of China, the nation's largest bank, became the first bank with
savings deposits of more than two trillion yuan, at the end of
June.
</P>
<P>
The amount of deposits by individuals was up 108.1 billion yuan
from the beginning of the year, while the bank's deposits from
different sources rose 147.6 billion yuan during the period.
</P>
<P>
"Our bank managed to have a rapidly growing business and
achieve favorable funds efficiency, in spite of growing
competition in the banking sector," said an ICBC official.
</P>
<P>
The bank also made 64.3 billion yuan more in loans than at the
year's opening, mainly to efficient enterprises with high credit
ratings.
</P>
<P>
The bank vowed to support these enterprises with more credit
and that large and medium-sized state enterprises in the
infrastructure sector and pillar industries will get more loans.
</P>
</TEXT>
