<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970716.0114 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Bans Illegal Dealings in Renminbi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 16 (Xinhua) -- The General Office of the State
Council has issued a circular, banning the illegal buying and
selling of renminbi (RMB), China's official currency.
</P>
<P>
Illegal dealing in RMB has affected the normal circulation
of currency and damaged its credit.
</P>
<P>
The circular said that dealing in RMB out of circulation
must be approved by the People's Bank of China. Without that,
institutions and individuals are not allowed to impose designs or
layouts on the currency, or deal in RMB in circulation.
</P>
<P>
Those caught violating the regulation will be subject to
confiscation of property by departments in charge of industrial
and commercial administration and other penalties.
</P>
<P>
Financial institutions and their employees are not allowed to
use their workplace to facilitate or participate in illegal
dealings in RMB, according to the circular.
</P>
<P>
The illegal buying and selling of foreign currencies inside
China will be handled in a similar way.  
</P>
