<HEADLINE> Israel Welcomes Cypriot Bi-communal Direct Talks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, July 16 (Xinhua) -- Israel has welcomed the opening of
direct talks between Cypriot President Glafcos Clerides and
Turkish Cypriot leader Rauf Denktash, expressing the hope they
will lead to a peaceful settlement of the protracted Cyprus
problem.
</P>
<P>
Cyprus News Agency reported today that a spokesman of the
Israeli Ministry of Foreign Affairs expressed his country's
congratulations to the leaders of the two communities for
attending the U.N.-sponsored direct talks held at Troutbeck, near
New York, from July 9 to 12.
</P>
<P>
"Israel congratulates the leaders upon the opening of the
talks and hopes that they will herald progress towards peaceful
solution of the conflict," the spokesman was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
The Israeli Foreign Ministry spokesman also noted "Israel has
always favored dialog and negotiation in order to settle the
conflicts on the island and establish a lasting peace."
</P>
<P>
Another round of direct talks between Clerides and Denktash is
expected to take place between August 11 and 16 in Switzerland.
</P>
<P>
The U.N.-sponsored talks are aimed at solving the Cyprus
problem which arose in 1974 when the island was divided after
Turkish troops took over the northern third of the island in the
wake of a pro-Greece coup in Nicosia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
