<HEADLINE> China's Top Legislator Meets Japanese Visitors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 16 (Xinhua) -- Qiao Shi, chairman of the Chinese
National People's Congress (NPC) Standing Committee, met with
Masayoshi Takemura, former leader of the Sakigake (Pioneer Party)
of Japan, and other Japanese guests here this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Qiao, also a Standing Committee Member of the Political Bureau of
the Communist Party of China (CPC) Central Committee, said this
year is the 25th anniversary of the normalization of the
diplomatic ties between China and Japan.
</P>
<P>
The bilateral relations are good on the whole, and the two
countries should further promote the good-neighborly friendship
and economic cooperation in a bid to enhance the bilateral ties,
Qiao said.
</P>
<P>
Masayoshi Takemura, also member of the Japanese House of
Representatives, once again congratulated Qiao on China's
resumption of exercise of sovereignty over Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Qiao expressed his thanks for this, saying that after that Hong
Kong's return to the motherland, work in various fields have
progressed smoothly, and he believed Hong Kong's long-term
prosperity and stability is guaranteed.
</P>
<P>
He also expressed appreciations to the Japanese side for their
participation in the economic development in north China's Shanxi
Province and a project which diverts water from the Yellow River
to the province.
</P>
<P>
The top legislator hoped that the bilateral friendly cooperation
will continue to be strengthened.
</P>
<P>
Masayoshi Takemura said that China's economic achievements have
left him a deep impression and he would continue working to
promote the Japan-China friendly relations.
</P>
<P>
Hu Fuguo, secretary of the CPC Shanxi Provincial Committee, and
Xue Rongzhe, vice-governor of the province, were among those
present at the meeting. 
