<HEADLINE> Death Toll Rises to 80 in Indonesia's Ferry Accident </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, July 16 (Xinhua) -- The death toll from a ferry
sinking accident on Sunday in Indonesia's North Sumatra province
rose to 80 as two more bodies were found today, local press
reported.
</P>
<P>
A search and rescue team of 20 specialists found the bodies of
the two victims this morning. The team has been trying to find
dozens of people still missing after the disaster, which occurred
on Sunday night when the boat, overloaded with about 200
passengers, sank in Toba Lake 100 meters off shore from the island
town of Tomok.
</P>
<P>
Police and government officials said the boat, which was
carrying residents back from a cultural festival in Parapat to
Tomok, should have had no more than 60 passengers on board.
</P>
<P>
Survivors said they heard the boat's hull breaking while it was
sailing in the middle of the lake. The boat went down in 60-meter
deep waters.
</P>
<P>
Minister of Transport Haryanto Dhanutirto has called for an
investigation into the accident, reports said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
