<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK Handover Stamps Yield Big Revenue </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 16 (Xinhua) -- Commemorative handover stamps
issued in the past two weeks have brought the Hong Kong Post
Office 656 million HK dollars (84 million U.S. dollars), a local
paper reported today.
</P>
<P>
A set of six stamps to mark the establishment of the Hong Kong
Special Administrative Region on July 1 yielded 517 million HK
dollars (66 million US dollars, while sales of stamps issued on
June 30, 1997, the last day of the British colonial rule in Hong
Kong, netted 139 million HK dollars (18 million U.S. dollars),
according to the South China Morning Post.
</P>
<P>
Postmaster General Robert Footman said that sales of
commemorative handover stamps could account for half of the
philatelic revenue of the Post Office for the whole year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
