<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Fashion Festival Opens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 16 (Xinhua) -- An international fashion trade
fair opened here today in the Hong Kong Convention and Exhibition
Center, drawing more than 370 exhibitors from all over the world.
</P>
<P>
Henry Tang, chairman of the Federation of Hong Kong Industry,
said at the opening ceremony that Hong Kong, with a total export
of 170 billion HK dollars (22 billion U.S. dollars) in 1996, is
the second largest clothing exporter in the world after China's
inland area.
</P>
<P>
The garment industry is still the largest foreign exchange
earner in Hong Kong, where many leading international labels are
manufactured and exhibited.
</P>
<P>
Tang said that Hong Kong garment manufacturers are well
positioned to tap the world largest market -- the inland
areas of China with 1.2 billion potential consumers.
</P>
<P>
Apart from catwalk shows, a young designers' contest and
seminars will also be held during the four-day fashion festival.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
