<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Press Welcomes Land Sales Program </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 16 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong major's newspapers
today devoted full pages to a massive land sales program unveiled
Tuesday by the Special Administrative Region (SAR) government.
</P>
<P>
Under the five-year program, the fresh land supply for the
private sector will reach 433 hectares, more than doubling the
total land supply over the past five years.
</P>
<P>
In the next 21 months, the SAR government is scheduled to sell
100 plots of public land, enough for the construction of nearly
65,000 flats.
</P>
<P>
"To improve the land supply is the only and fundamental way to
ease the surge of housing prices," the Hong Kong Daily News said
in a commentary.
</P>
<P>
Wen Wei Po's commentary said the sufficient supply of land
shows that the SAR government is determined to meet Chief
Executive Tung Chee Hwa's objective to increase the overall annual
supply to not less than 85,000 units in the next five years.
</P>
<P>
"The land sales program is also good news for industrial and
commercial investors in Hong Kong. The rocketing property prices
have somewhat weakened the competitive edge of Hong Kong," the
newspaper said.
</P>
<P>
Tin Tin Daily said The SAR government is now taking the first
step to tackle the housing problem which has aroused general
concern. The plan to increase the land supply has brought hopes to
the local people, who have long-cherished dreams to have their own
houses.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
