<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Anti-Piracy Campaign Fruitful </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 16 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong Customs has seized
more than 46,400 illicit compact discs in a recent anti-piracy
operation, the Government Information Services reported today.
</P>
<P>
Officers of the Intellectual Property Investigation Bureau
raided 17 shops in Kowloon Tuesday and captured 46,400 pirated
compact discs worth 1.8 million HK dollars (230,000 U.S.
dollars).
</P>
<P>
A Customs spokesman said that it was the third day of the
operation dubbed "Thunderbolt", launched to clear copyright
infringing goods from the local retail market.
</P>
<P>
During the three-day operation, the Customs seized a total of
266,200 pieces of pirated goods valued at nine million HK dollars
(1.15 million U.S. dollars), and arrested 100 suspects. 
</P>
</TEXT>
