<HEADLINE> Chinese Vice-President Meets Japanese Guests </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 16 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-President Rong Yiren
met with Takahiro Yokomichi, deputy leader of the Democratic Party
of Japan (DPJ), and his party here today.
</P>
<P>
Rong appreciated the positive contributions Yokomichi has made
over years to the cause of Sino-Japanese friendship and the DPJ's
stance of taking a correct approach toward the history and
developing Sino-Japanese friendly ties.
</P>
<P>
The friendly and cooperative relations has been developing
rapidly since the diplomatic ties of the two countries were
normalized 25 years ago, Rong said, adding that it is the set
policy of the Chinese government to enhance bilateral relations
and the two sides should face the 21st century and work together,
so as to contribute to the world peace and stability and the
happiness of the humanity.
</P>
<P>
Yokomichi, who is also member of the Japanese House of
Representatives, said he has come to visit China on the occasion
of the 25 anniversary of the normalization of diplomatic ties
between Japan and China, expressing his conviction that the
bilateral ties will develop constantly.
</P>
<P>
The DPJ hopes to enhance non-governmental contacts, especially
those between the young people, in the wake of continuous
expansion of exchanges between the two governments, Yokomichi
added.
</P>
<P>
Rong agreed with Yokomichi on enhancement of non-governmental
contacts, especially those between the young people, which he said
is of great importance to the development of bilateral relations and
friendship from generation to generation.
</P>
<P>
Rong expressed the hope that Japanese statesmen and personnel
in all walks of life will do more in this regard and make new
contributions to the cause of Sino-Japanese friendship.
</P>
<P>
Rong also briefed the guests on China's economic development.
</P>
<P>
Qi Huaiyuan, president of the Chinese People's Association for
Friendship with Foreign Countries, was present at the meeting.
</P>
<P>
Japanese guests arrived here yesterday as guests of the China-Japan
Friendship Association. 
</P>
</TEXT>
