<HEADLINE> Share Prices Continue to Decline on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, July 16 (Xinhua) -- Share prices continue to decline
sharply on the Singapore market as the benchmark Straits Times
Industrials Index lost another 19.2 points to close at 1917.89
today.
</P>
<P>
Total market volume stood at 127.3 million units, worth 308.54
million Singapore dollars (about 214.26 million U.S. dollars).
Declines continued to lead advances by 166 to 135, while 328 other
counters remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
QAF Ltd. was the most actively traded stock as it registered a
turnover of 4.96 million units. It was followed by the Raffles
Medical Group which had 4.92 million shares traded. Huan Hsin was
next with 4.78 million shares changed hands.
</P>
<P>
Local computer sound card maker Creative 50 led the gainers of
the day as it surged 2.1 dollars to finish at 31.9 Singapore
dollars. The DBS (Development Bank of Singapore) Foreign, GE Life,
and the SPH (Singapore Press Holdings) Foreign rose 40 cents each
to end at 18.8, 16.9 and 28 Singapore dollars respectively.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, local car distributor Cycle &AMP; Carriage (C&AMP;C)
was the biggest loser as it shed 60 cents to end at 12.6 Singapore
dollars. KL Kepong fell 36 cents to close at 3.1 dollars, while HL
CreRS100 finished 30 cents lower at 0.4 dollars.  
</P>
</TEXT>
