<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Vietnam Launches Independent Narcotics Department </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, July 16 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam has set up an independent
police department to deal with the nation's growing drug
trafficking and drug-related crimes, local press reported today.
</P>
<P>
The new police body, called the Narcotics Department, made its
first public appearance at the headquarters of the People's Police
General Department here on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The narcotics police used to be part of the economic police,
one of the several departments under the People's Police General
Department of the Ministry of the Interior.
</P>
<P>
The Narcotics Department is responsible for combating drug
trafficking and related crimes and providing advice to the
director of the People's Police General Department on how to
involve the general population in this battle.
</P>
<P>
The new department said it was going to recruit enough staff to
man stations to be set up across the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
