<DOCNO> XIE19970716.0146 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-16 09:28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Iran to Stage Military Maneuvers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, July 16 (Xinhua) -- Some 20,000 Iranian military
forces are to launch a two-day maneuvers from July 31 to August 1
in Iran's southwestern province of Chaharmahal-Bakhtiyari, a
local newspaper reported today.
</P>
<P>
The Persian daily Jomhuri Islami said that the maneuvers,
code-named Ashura, will be jointly launched by the Islamic
Revolution Guards Corps (IRGC) and the grassroots mobilization
forces, including women's battalions named Az-Zahra.
</P>
<P>
"The most active forces chosen during these maneuvers will
take part in the Fat-Hol-Mobin (Manifest Victory) grand maneuvers
which will be held before March 21, 1998," Brigadier Gholmreza
Solaymani was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
However, the report did not mention what kind of weapons will
be used and what purposes of the war games.
</P>
<P>
According to Iran's official news agency IRNA, the army's
ground forces have actively controlled any "unauthorized movement"
in the southern and western borders of the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
