<HEADLINE> Closer Links Expected Between Japan and Gansu </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LANZHOU, July 16 (Xinhua) -- Thanks to the westward shift of
the State economic construction focus, Gansu has become a popular
destination for foreign investment.
</P>
<P>
A delegation of the Osaka Chamber of Commerce and Industry from
Japan, headed by Hotta Teruo, recently inspected Lanzhou, capital
of Gansu Province, in northwest China. Before coming to Lanzhou,
the delegation made an on-the-spot inspection of some other cities
in western China such as Chongqing, Chengdu and Urumqi.
</P>
<P>
After extensive discussions with officials and entrepreneurs in
the province, delegates said they had gained a better
understanding of investment policies and major fields of
investment available to them in the area.
</P>
<P>
They showed great interest in working with Gansu in the sectors
of retail trade, automobile and woollen textile.
</P>
<P>
Japan has been the fourth largest trade partner of Gansu. It
has built 59 enterprises there involving a total investment of
16.6 million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Both sides have had successful partnerships in the fields of
education, scientific research, agriculture, water conservancy,
preservation of cultural relics and control of shifting sands.
</P>
<P>
Hotta Teruo noted after the inspection tour that the Chinese
government's attention to the economic development in the central
and western parts of the country has won the confidence of
Japanese businessmen.
</P>
<P>
He said his delegation was deeply impressed by the great
improvements made in the fields of transportation and
telecommunication in these cities in recent years.
</P>
<P>
He promised to organize more delegates from small and
medium-sized enterprises to visit this area in future. 
</P>
</TEXT>
