<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, July 16 (Xinhua) -- Tourist arrivals in the Philippines
rose by 10 percent to 705,800 during the first four months of this
year, the Philippine News Agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
The agency quoted a report by the Department of Tourism as
saying that the bulk of the tourists came from East Asia,
especially from Japan, while the United States was the biggest
market for the Philippines' tourism among the western countries.
</P>
<P>
The report also said that many foreign investors have found
that
taking the tourist route is one of the most effective ways of
getting to
know the Philippines.
</P>
<P>
Currently, the growing trend among potential foreign investors
is to come to the country first as tourists, check the business
climate and then come back purely on a business trip, the report
said.  
</P>
