<HEADLINE> Education in Patriotism Stressed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 16 (Xinhua) -- Chi Haotian, vice-chairman of the
Central Military Commission, today emphasized the need to educate
people about the country's national defense system, paying
particular attention to patriotism.
</P>
<P>
Chi, also state councillor and minister of National Defense,
said that "the invigoration of the Chinese nation and the
reunification of the country require a powerful national defense
system."
</P>
<P>
Chi made the remarks while granting awards to a number of
departments in charge of education in national defense, as well as
some media and publishing organizations.
</P>
<P>
"Following more than 100 years of vicissitude, Hong Kong has
returned smoothly to China. The fundamental reason for its return
now is the strength of our country, including the strength of its
national defense," Chi said.
</P>
<P>
Though now is a time of great happiness in China, he reminded
people of the suffering caused by imperialist powers, China's
history of humiliation, and the sacred mission of safeguarding
national sovereignty, security and long-term stability with a
powerful defense system.
</P>
<P>
"In China today, patriotism is the love of socialist China
under the leadership by the Chinese Communist Party," he said,
calling for continued efforts to carry on the fine traditions of
the Chinese nation, safeguard national sovereignty, and contribute
to the socialist cause.
</P>
<P>
To strengthen national defense is the duty of all government
departments, social institutions, businesses and citizens. Only
when the entire society pays attention to, cherishes and
supports national defense can the defense system become strong in
the real sense, Chi said.
</P>
<P>
Buhe, vice-chairman of the National People's Congress (NPC)
Standing Committee, and Zhu Guangya, vice-chairman of the National
Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative
Conference (CPPCC), were present at the ceremony. 
</P>
</TEXT>
