<HEADLINE> New Bond Market Has Smooth Operation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 16 (Xinhua) -- The one-month old national
inter-bank bond trading system reported smooth operations and
active trading during the past 22 trading days.
</P>
<P>
Total turnover with the bond trading system amounted to 7.791
billion yuan, which broke down into 121 million yuan in spot
trading and 7.67 yuan in repurchasing volume.
</P>
<P>
The gross figure also translated into a daily average of 350
million yuan.
</P>
<P>
Analysts said that the repurchasing mainly occurred in the
short-term policy-oriented financial bonds, with the repurchasing
interest rate generally below the rate on the inter-bank money
market and the past repurchasing rate of treasury bonds on the
stock exchanges.
</P>
<P>
But they said the inter-bank bond trading market still needs to
expand further and have more active trading.
</P>
<P>
Banks also expressed the hope that the policy-oriented
financial bonds may become tradable and open market operation be
adopted to expand the market and improve its liquidity.  
</P>
</TEXT>
