<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, July 16 (Xinhua) -- Zimbabwean parliament on Tuesday
passed an emergency motion appealing to president Robert Mugabe
to meet ex-combatants who have staged a series of demonstrations
countrywide demanding payments under the beleaguered war victims
compensation fund.
</P>
<P>
In heated contributions to the motion by member of parliament
Jacobus De Wetg, the legislators, most of them also
ex-combatants, said only the president could solve the plight of
war veterans.
</P>
