<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Uganda's Cement Production Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, July 16 (Xinhua) -- Cement production from Uganda's
two major cement factories rehabilitated in recent years has
greatly increased, reported the local newspaper, The People,
today.
</P>
<P>
The production at Hima Cement Factory has increased from
42,378 tons in 1994 to 112,697 tons in 1996 and is expected to
achieve full production of 450,000 tons this year.
</P>
<P>
The production at Tororo Cement Works has increased from 2,094
tons in June 1996 to 10,425 tons last month after the
installation of new machinery.
</P>
<P>
Currently Uganda consumes 300,000 tons to 350,000 tons of
cement annually.
</P>
<P>
With the quick cement production increase in recent years,
Uganda will become self-sufficiency in cement supply very soon.
</P>
</TEXT>
