<HEADLINE> Tanzania Earns 322 Million Dollars From Tourist </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, July 16 (Xinhua) -- Tanzania has realised a
considerable tourist revenue collection to the tune of 322.38
million US Dollars in the 1996/97 fiscal year, while 258.14
million US Dollars were recorded in the previous year, local
press reported today.
</P>
<P>
The Principal Tourist Information Officer of the Tanzania
Tourist Board (TTB), Johnson Manase, told reporters here on
Tuesday that the number of tourists arrivals rose from 293,834
people in 1995/96 to 326,194 people in 1996/97, with increased
rate of 11.1 percent between the two fiscal years.
</P>
<P>
The TTB officer further said the introduction of visa at the
main gate ways (at the border) launched early this year has
greatly reduced the bureaucracy that existed previously.
</P>
<P>
Commenting on the problems facing the tourist sector, he said
poor infrastructural design in some tourist areas was the main
problem in the country, citing an example of the poor
Makuyuni-Ngorongoro road in Arusha, northern Tanzania. 
</P>
