<HEADLINE> Chinese Bank Improves Efficiency Through Cost Control </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 16 (Xinhua) -- The Agricultural Bank of China has
issued a circular urging tighter control over the construction
projects at its branches and operations across the country.
</P>
<P>
The circular forbids all the ABC branches to build new office
buildings or expand, rebuild or refurnish the existing office
buildings.
</P>
<P>
Any building projects that haven't started construction will be
put on hold, said the circular, which also clamps down on the
opening of new banking operations across the nation.
</P>
<P>
A list of Dos and Don'ts has been imposed on the ongoing
building projects, which prohibits the use of imported decoration
materials and calls for practical and efficient use of funds for
such projects.
</P>
<P>
The circular also requires all the ABC branch banks to strictly
abide by a financial management system concerning the building of
office towers.  
</P>
</TEXT>
