<HEADLINE> Tourist Activities Diverse at Seaside Qingdao </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QINGDAO, July 16 (Xinhua) -- The scenic seaside city of Qingdao
has emerged as a leading Chinese tourist destination with a
colorful range of sites and activities for visitors.
</P>
<P>
Long known as a sightseers' paradise, Qingdao in east China's
Shandong Province has become a likely choice for vacationers and
people on business trips.
</P>
<P>
With a combination of Chinese and Western architecture and
beautiful hilly and beach front scenery, the well-preserved old
urban area of Qingdao is also popular, and travelers there can visit
historic buildings, museums, cathedrals, shop at trendy department
stores, and swim in the sea.
</P>
<P>
The Taoist temples at Mount Laoshan, located about 30
kilometers away, are also a favorite.
</P>
<P>
People making return visits to Qingdao are usually surprised to
see how the city's beautiful coastline has been extended as a
result of the emergence of the new business area to the east which
is lined with skyscrapers.
</P>
<P>
Five-star hotels with all the amenities have been built in this
area, as well as holiday resorts complete with golf courses.
</P>
<P>
The annual "Qingdao International Beer Festival" held in
summer has also become a big draw for both Chinese and foreign
beer lovers and investors.
</P>
<P>
Latest figures show that in the first five months of this year,
Qingdao received 61,306 overseas tourists who generated tourism
earnings of 28.09 million US dollars, a rise of 13.34 percent and
12.4 percent, respectively, over the same period last year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
