<HEADLINE> China to Maintain Land Contract System </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 16 (Xinhua) -- China will continue to implement
the contract household responsibility system in its rural areas
for another 30 years, the latest issue Business News quoted
Minister of Agriculture Liu Jiang as saying.
</P>
<P>
He made this remark during a recently convened meeting that was
attended by heads of agricultural departments from 31 provinces,
municipalities and autonomous regions.
</P>
<P>
The country's general economic conditions were satisfactory in
the first half of this year with the output of summer grain
reaching a record high, Jiang said. He noted that China's grain
stock has reached internationally standardized "safe line," with
its population securing an average per capita grain of 400 kg..
</P>
<P>
He attributed these unprecedented achievements to the household
contract responsibility system that benefits both farmers and the
country.
</P>
<P>
Jiang also stressed that local governments should guide farmers
to invest in sideline product processing industries and protect
farmers' enthusiasm for production by deepening reforms in the
sales and marketing of farm products.  
</P>
</TEXT>
