<HEADLINE> Asia-Africa Forum on Women Opens in Thailand </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, July 16 (Xinhua) -- About 100 women representatives
from 18 African and 13 Asian countries began a three-day forum
here today to exchange information and experiences on the economic
empowerment of women.
</P>
<P>
The forum responds to the recommendations of the 1995 Beijing
Declaration and Platform for Action and a few other declarations
on women adopted in recent years in Tokyo and Accra.
</P>
<P>
The documents called upon women entrepreneurs, the government
and the international community to remove barriers and promote the
economic equality of women through information networks, lobbying
coalition, capacity building, direct investments and access to
information and technology.
</P>
<P>
The objectives of the forum are to initiate collaborative
efforts for the economic empowerment of women and create policy
frameworks conducive to these ends.
</P>
<P>
The forum is co-sponsored by the governments of Japan and
Thailand, The United Nations Development Program, and the U.N.
Office of the Special Coordinator for Africa and the Least
Developed Countries (UNOSCAL).  
</P>
