<HEADLINE> Russia's Economic Situation Turns Better </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, July 15 (Xinhua) -- Russia's industrial production
increased slightly in the first half of the year but the economic
situation remains critical, according to an economic report
released by the State Statistical committee today.
</P>
<P>
Industrial output rose by 0.8 percent, representing an increase
for the first time in six years but the gross domestic product
dropped by 0.2 percent from the same period last year, the highest
drop in six years, the report said.
</P>
<P>
The rise in industrial output is mainly attributed to the
increase in production by small firms and joint ventures, economic
analysts said. The production of large and medium-sized
enterprises however dropped by 0.9 percent.
</P>
<P>
The output of Pharmaceutical industry rose by 9 percent, the
highest among the growth rates of all industries, while production
in chemical, petrochemical, non-ferrous, metallurgical, machine
building, and metal processing sectors increased by a range from
0.7 to 2.0 percent.
</P>
<P>
But production in the sectors of power generation, fuel, steel
and iron, forestry, building materials, foodstuffs and light
industry dropped with ranges from 0.8 to 7.0 percent.
</P>
<P>
From January to June, the country generated 423 billion
kilowatt hours of electricity, produced 147 million tons of oil
and 282 billion cubic meters of natural gas, mined 125 million
tons of coal, and produced 18.6 million tons of steel products,
460,000 cars, 71,000 trucks and 63,000 personal computers, the
report said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
