<DOCNO> XIE19970716.0221 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Species Face Threat in Antarctica </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, July 15 (Xinhua) -- Pollution and poaching in the
Antarctic pose a serious threat to fish and migratory birds there,
scientists warned today.
</P>
<P>
Scientists from the University of Auckland in New Zealand
discovered a large number of sick fish close to the McMurdo Base,
in the Antarctic. The sickness was caused by pollution created by
human activities.
</P>
<P>
The population of McMurdo Base, by the Ross Ice Shelf, grew to
1,000 people in summer and today there are tons of fuel, machinery
and all kinds of garbage in the region.
</P>
<P>
Specialists said that the low temperature in the Antarctic
impeded the normal growth of micro organisms that degrade wastes.
So all the rubbish dumped there maintained its toxic potential for
several years.
</P>
<P>
Another threat to species is hunting. Owing to this, masses of
migratory birds disappeared, United States scientists said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970716.0222 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Central American Borders to Remain Open 24 Hours a Day </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANAGUA, July 15 (Xinhua) -- As part of the integration
program, customs and migratory services on the borders of the
Central American countries will operate 24 hours a day starting
August 15, Nicaragua's Press Secretariat said today.
</P>
<P>
The measure, initiated by Nicaraguan President Arnoldo Aleman,
was approved at a summit of Central American presidents held in
Panama last weekend.
</P>
<P>
"One thing that took off at the summit and sparked a lot of
interest was the idea of keeping Central American and Panamanian
borders open 24 hours a day," said Aleman upon his return from
Panama.
</P>
<P>
"All six countries, Costa Rica, Guatemala, Honduras, Nicaragua,
El Salvador and Panama, are in agreement with this course of
action, which will facilitate the job of truck drivers," said the
president.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that it is going to save a lot of money for the
truck drivers of the region who used to have to wait a long time
until the borders were opened. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
