<HEADLINE> Colombia's Fiscal Deficit to Increase In 1998 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTAFE DE BOGOTA, July 15 (Xinhua) -- Colombia's central bank
predicted that the country's fiscal deficit will increase next
year, a national media said today.
</P>
<P>
It estimated that the deficit for the federal government
will be 5 percent and that for the public sector 3 percent.
</P>
<P>
At present, both figures are 1 percent lower.
</P>
<P>
Salomon Kalmanovitz, co-director of the Banco de la Republica,
called on the government to reduce the deficit by cutting down
expenditure.
</P>
<P>
"The government needs to reduce its fiscal deficit by cutting
out every expenditure that does not contribute to production,"
Kalmanovitz told a seminar.
</P>
<P>
The banker also asked the government to "conscientiously
review" the foreign debt figure next year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
