<HEADLINE> Ukraine, U.S. Black Sea Exercise To Go Ahead </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, July 15 (Xinhua) -- Ukraine will launch Sea Breeze-97
naval exercise with the United States and other North Atlantic
Treaty Organization navies as scheduled, from August 25 to 31.
</P>
<P>
Ukrainian Defense Minister Alexander Kuzmuk said on Tuesday
that the Black Sea exercise aims to provide humanitarian aid after
devastating earthquakes in nearby countries.
</P>
<P>
Every preparation for the operation has been completed, he said.
</P>
<P>
The exercise will be held within the framework of the Program
for Peaceful Partnership, Kuzmuk told a parliament meeting.
</P>
<P>
The leftists-dominated parliament is now planning a law which
will prevent NATO forces staging maneuvers in Ukraine. The defense
minister made a speech in an effort to stop the adoption of the
law.
</P>
<P>
"Ukraine's non-alignment and neutrality status does not mean
that we should completely refuse military cooperation with other
countries," Kuzmuk said.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, the exercise will be solely sponsored by the United
States, and Ukraine does not need to spend a cent, he added. The
U.S. force will include marines and ships from the U.S. Sixth
Fleet. 
</P>
</TEXT>
