<HEADLINE> East China Province to Open Wider to Outside World </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 16 (Xinhua) -- East China's coastal province of
Shandong will adopt a series of new measures to gear up the local
economic growth by further opening to the outside world and
expanding channels for overseas funds, today's "China Daily"
reported.
</P>
<P>
Shandong must seize the present opportunity to push its economy
forward by internationalizing the local economy, the paper quoted
Wu Guanzheng, secretary of the provincial Committee of the Chinese
Communist Party, as saying.
</P>
<P>
Wu called on local leading officials to pay closer attention
to the open-up efforts and introduce more overseas funds into
projects with higher economic returns.
</P>
<P>
Some local state enterprises should enhance their economic
strength by making full use of overseas funds and resources, in a
bid to increase their shares of overseas markets, said Wu.
</P>
<P>
In addition to the export of local traditional products, mostly
farm and sideline products, the province will increase the
shipment of high-value-added and manufactured products, instead of
selling its raw materials and primary products as in the past.
</P>
<P>
Local authorities are also urged to adopt much more flexible
policies, in a bid to enable the province to increase the direct
use of overseas funds.
</P>
<P>
Wu said that some of the province's state enterprises will be
turned into joint-stock companies to allow overseas investors to
buy shares, and others will be jointly selling stocks abroad to
raise badly needed funds. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
