<HEADLINE> Grand Trade Fair Set to Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 16 (Xinhua) -- Guangzhou, capital of south
China's Guangdong province, is to hold a grand fair named '97
Guangzhou Fair, from July 17 to July 22, today's "China Daily"
reports.
</P>
<P>
The paper quotes Dai Donghe, director of the fair as saying
that the event aims to consolidate domestic and international
economic co-operation, promote economic, technological and
cultural exchange, and bolster the development of trade
domestically and internationally.
</P>
<P>
The fair will offer 850 stands, over 100 of which are to be
occupied by foreign exhibitors, the rest being shared by domestic
exhibitors.
</P>
<P>
The fair will highlight new products, specialty products and
brand names. It will also focus on Chinese products. Single-line
exhibitions will be one of the fair's features. It will offer an
opportunity for business people to forge economic and
technological links.
</P>
<P>
The fair will provide a list of over 1,000 projects for
potential co-operation, including those related to the mechanical
and electrical industries, the chemical industry, food,
metallurgy, real estate and infrastructure, the paper says.
