<HEADLINE> Schumacher Blows up Tire During Tests </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, July 15 (Xinhua) -- Two-time world Formula One champion
Michael Schumacher of Germany blew out a tire of his Ferrari
during tests at Italy's Monza circuit on Tuesday but managed to
control the car and avoided to spin off the track, reports said
here on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
A witness was quoted by the Italian news agency ANSA as saying
that the rear right tire blew out as Schumacher was approaching
the Lesmo corner at about 300 kph.
</P>
<P>
The Ferrari driver, current leader of the world championship
standings, then drove slowly to the pits and stopped the tests.
</P>
<P>
Schumacher and the Ferrari team started on Tuesday three days
of tests at the Monza track in preparation for the next
championship race at Hockenheim, Germany. 
</P>
