<HEADLINE> Srecki Wins Second World Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, July 15 (Xinhua) -- Former Olympic champion Erick
Sreck of France captured his second world title in the men's epee
in Cape Town, South Africa, on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
He defeated twice world champion Pavel Kolobkov of Russia
15-14 after forcing the bout into extra time by scoring an
equalising hit four seconds from the end of the final period.
</P>
<P>
Italy's Giovanna Trillini scored a more comfortable women's
foil victory over Germany's veteran Sabine Bau to add a world
crown to the one she won in 1991. Trillini cruised home 15-10.
