<HEADLINE> Defending Champion Schett Advances In Palermo Tennis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, July 15 (Xinhua) -- Defending champion Barbara Schett of
Austria reached the second round of the WTA tournament in Palermo,
Sicily, on Tuesday after her rival Silka Meier of Germany retired
with an injury.
</P>
<P>
Top-seeded Barbara Paulus also won her first round in the
middle when fellow Austrian Sandra Dopfer withdrew down 2-1 in the
second set with a sore shoulder. Paulus had won the first set 7-5.
</P>
<P>
Schett, seeded third, was leading 6-1, 1-0 when a hand injury
stopped the German continuing.
</P>
<P>
Sandra Cecchini and Laura Garrone both defeated their opponents
before home fans, with Cecchini beating Maria Jose Gaidano of
Argentina 6-4, 6-3 and Garrone ousting Lenka Cenkova of the Czech
Republic 6-7 (8-6), 6-2, 6-4.
</P>
<P>
In the other matches, fourth seed Argentine Florencia Labat
outplayed Fabiola Zuluaa of Colombia 3-6, 6-2, 6-0 while
sixth-seeded Virginia Ruano-Pascual of Spain beat Lenka Nemeckova
of the Czech Republic 7-6 (7-0), 6-3. 
</P>
