<HEADLINE> Jansher Khan May Miss Australian Open Squash </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KARACHI, July 15 (Xinhua) -- World number one Jansher Khan said
Tuesday he would miss the Australian Open Squash because his
pregnant wife was sick.
</P>
<P>
"She is pregnant and having problems. I cannot leave her when
she needs me," Khan told AFP.
</P>
<P>
But the squash superstar hit out at suggestions that he was
deliberately avoiding the event because of past rivalry with
Australians.
</P>
<P>
"I am a professional squash player and want to perform my skill
before my fans all over the world. I am still available for the
tournament if the organisers can delay the tournament for another
two weeks," he said.
</P>
<P>
"I have withdrawn for personal reasons and it is not that I
have some jealousy or enmity with anybody."
</P>
<P>
Khan said he would play in the World Games in Finland starting
August 11. "I am going there because of my country. I will play
there for free, there is no money involved."
</P>
<P>
"I have agreed to play to promote squash as I can see that
squash will be included in the Olympics, if not in 2000 then in
2004." 
</P>
</TEXT>
