<HEADLINE> Export Commodity Fair Opens in Northeast China City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DALIAN, July 16 (Xinhua) -- The 1997 Dalian Export Commodity
Fair, the second largest of its kind in China, opened Tuesday in
this coastal city of northeast China's Liaoning Province.
</P>
<P>
The seven-day fair is the first regional fair held in
China's inland areas since the return of Hong Kong on July 1. The
event has attracted 16 companies from Hong Kong, organized by the
Hong Kong Trade Development Council.
</P>
<P>
In addition, about 542 domestic companies and enterprises and
some 3,000 overseas business people from many countries, including
Japan, the ROK, the US, Italy, and Germany, are participating.
</P>
<P>
The first Dalian fair was held in 1987. 
</P>
