<HEADLINE> Singapore Company Sets Up Tourist Resort in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 16 (Xinhua) -- Prime Group International of
Singapore has put 100 million US dollars into a 160-ha holiday
resort, "Sun Island", in Shanghai, China's industrial and
commercial center.
</P>
<P>
Supreme Head of Malaysia Tuanku Ja'afar visited the resort
yesterday.
</P>
<P>
"Sun Island", in Qingpu County, Shanghai, has three rivers
running across it and is the largest holiday resort in this
largest industrial and commercial city.
</P>
<P>
