<HEADLINE> Kuerten Reaches Third Round in Stuttgart </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, July 15 (Xinhua) -- French Open champion Gustavo Kuerten
of Brazil fought back to beat local favorite Jens Knippschild 6-7
(4-7), 6-4, 6-4 to reach the third round of the one million
U.S. dollars Mercedes Cup in Stuttgart, Germany, on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Knippschild's loss was the sixth of the German players
following the elimination of Nicolas Kiefer, Daniel Elsner, Alex
Radulescu, qualifier Martin Sinner and Marc Goellner.
</P>
<P>
Wimbledon quarter-finalist Kiefer fell and twisted his right
ankle while chasing a volley at the start of the fourth game of
his opening set with Karol Kucera of Slovakia. He was forced to
withdraw.
</P>
<P>
Radulescu was beaten 6-1, 6-3 by Brazilian Fernando
Meligeni. Junior Wimbledon finalist Elsner went out 6-3, 6-4 to
Swede Magnus Larsson.
</P>
<P>
Second seed Alex Corretja dispatched Goellner 7-5, 6-1 and
Wayne Ferreira, the South African 14th seed, defeated Sinner 3-6,
6-0, 6-4.
</P>
<P>
In sharp contrast to Germany, the Spaniards tasted all-round
victories in the day's competition.
</P>
<P>
In addition to Corretja's win, Francisco Clavet outplayed
veteran Magnus Gustafsson of Sweden 6-3, 1-6, 6-1 and Javier
Sanchez beat another Swede Magnus Norman 6-3, 7-6 (7-4).
</P>
<P>
Galo Blanco eliminated Hicham Arazi of Morocco 7-5, 7-6 (7-4)
in a battle of French Open quarter-finalists, while Albert Portas
handed Norway's Christian Ruud a 5-7, 6-0, 7-6 (7-2) defeat.
</P>
</TEXT>
