<HEADLINE> Ullrich Clinches 10th Stage in Tour de France </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PAIRS, July 15 (Xinhua) -- Jan Ullrich took a firm grip of the
Tour de France with a magnificent finish on the final climb of the
10th stage from Arcalis to Andorra on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The German left his Telekom team leader and defending
champion Bjarne Riis and French challenger Richard Virenque in
his wake and surged to victory in the 252.5 km stage from Luchon
to Arcalis by one minute eight seconds.
</P>
<P>
Marco Pantani of Italy was second and Virenque third.
</P>
<P>
Ullrich gained overall leadership from Cedric Vasseur of France
and showed the potential to keep it for the remainder of the race.


