<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Al-Hareth Wins First Gold for Hosts Lebanon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, July 15 (Xinhua) -- Saoud al-Hareth threw 40.22 meters
in the women's javelin to win the first gold for hosts Lebanon
in the Arab Games here on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
But the result was 13.02m shy than the Games record set by
Syria's world and Olympic heptathlon champion Ghada Chouaa.
</P>
<P>
Egypt continued its success with the start of the weightlifting
competition. Egypt won five weightlifting golds and took another
in the hammer by Charif Hennaoui to take first place in the medals
table with nine golds.
</P>
<P>
Algeria, second in the table with eight golds, took two on
Tuesday in the women's high jump through Hamida Ben Hassan and
women's foil fencing with Wassila Radouane.
</P>
<P>
Morocco's women athletes showed their prowess on the track,
with Hasna Ben Hassi winning the 800 meters and Fatiha Aklileche
taking the 10,000 meters. 
</P>
</TEXT>
