<HEADLINE> Aussie Upstarts Stuns Sixth Seed Roux </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 15 (Xinhua) -- Australia's 620th-ranked Luke
Smith scored a surprise win over sixth seed Lionel Roux here
Tuesday to reach the third round of the 675,000 U.S. dollars
Washington Classic tennis tournament.
</P>
<P>
The 20-year-old Smith, who won the United States collegiate
singles and doubles titles in May, dropped only five points on his
own serve in disposing of the 65th-ranked Frenchman 6-3, 6-3.
</P>
<P>
Smith, who was making his ATP debut, will next face either
83rd-rated Brett Steven of New Zealand or 166th-rated Russian
Andre Merinov.
</P>
<P>
Seeded Aussies Jason Stoltenberg and Scott Draper also
advanced. Fifth seed Stoltenberg beat Russia's Andre Cherkasov
6-2, 6-3 while seventh seed Draper eliminated France's Gerard
Solves 7-5, 6-1.
</P>
<P>
Second seed Petr Korda of the Czech Republic also booked a
third round berth after ousting South Africa's David Nainkin 6-4,
6-2.  
</P>
