<HEADLINE> Donors Conference for Bosnia Scheduled for Late July </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SARAJEVO, July 15 (Xinhua) -- The much-delayed international
conference to raise reconstruction funds for Bosnia has been
re-scheduled for July 23-24 in Brussels, it was reported on
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Local media reports here said the date has been confirmed by
the World Bank, which together with the European Union has
organized the so-called donors conference to be attended by more
than 50 countries.
</P>
<P>
It is expected to raise 1.4 billion U.S. dollars at the meeting
to meet Bosnia's reconstruction needs for the next year, bringing
to the total of international pledge to the country to 2.2 billion
dollars.
</P>
<P>
Originally scheduled for early this year, the conference has
been repeatedly postponed because Bosnian parties failed to meet
the conditions set by Western donors, such as the passage of a
package of legislation necessary as the basis of unitary country.
</P>
