<HEADLINE> U.S. Plane Catches Fire Before Take-off </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 15 (Xinhua) -- All the 81 passengers and five
crew members were forced to evacuate a DC-9 jet today when one of
the plane's engines caught fire at Logan International Airport in
Boston, a northeastern coast city of the United States.
</P>
<P>
The engine of the U.S. Air Flight 1505, departing Boston for
Pittsburgh, burst into flames as it backed away from the gate at
about 3:30 p.m. local time (1930 GMT).
</P>
<P>
Most passengers evacuated on the slides set up from the
emergency exits, but some jumped to the ground from the wings. At
least eight people were injured in the evacuation.
</P>
<P>
The flames were knocked down within minutes by firefighters
and U.S. Federal Aviation Administration officials are
investigating the cause of the fire. 
</P>
</TEXT>
